<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[192,1440,1564,1686]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,1564,1588]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Poros translúcidos en fémur y tibia; poros discoidales sobre superficie membranosa alrededor de los ojos; 2(1–4) conductos con collar oral ventrales cercanos al C6 y 2(0–5) asociados a C7 y C8; 1(0–3) setas auxiliares y 10(5–15) poros triloculares en C6; antena 411(341–452) μm de largo; fémur 239(217–267) μm; tibia 265(237–284) μm de largo y tarso 93(79–104) (tomado de Gimpel y Miller 1996).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[192,1440,1709,1929]" lastBlockId="30.[192,1440,217,375]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,1709,1733]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Discusión.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="1973" box="[342,613,1710,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eriocerei">
<emphasis box="[342,613,1710,1734]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Pseudococcus eriocerei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fue encontrada, hasta el momento, sólo en la raíz de cactáceas de 
<collectingCountry name="Argentina" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
la 
<taxonomicName box="[192,320,1742,1766]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Argentina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="29" pageNumber="-1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Argentina</taxonomicName>
</collectingCountry>
. Se aproxima a 
<taxonomicName authority="(Signoret)" authorityName="Coccoidea" baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[513,764,1742,1766]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viburni">
<emphasis box="[513,635,1742,1766]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. viburni</emphasis>
(Signoret)
</taxonomicName>
porque presenta 17 pares de cerarios, poros en fémur y tibia y carece de conductos con borde oral entre C2 y C3. Difiere de ella porque posee 1) escasos conductos con collar oral en vientre entre zona cefálica y C6 (numerosos en 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coccoidea" baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[999,1122,1807,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viburni">
<emphasis box="[999,1122,1807,1831]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. viburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 2) 1–4 setas cisvulvares (3–5 en 
<emphasis box="[288,418,1839,1863]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coccoidea" baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[288,410,1839,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viburni">P. viburni</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
3) 0–42 poros translúcidos en fémur posterior (15–150 en 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coccoidea" baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[1123,1245,1839,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viburni">
<emphasis box="[1123,1245,1839,1863]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. viburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); y 4) conductos tubulares con borde oral laterales y submediales en segmentos II y III del abdomen dorsal (ausentes en 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coccoidea" baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[192,315,1904,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viburni">
<emphasis box="[192,315,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. viburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). A simple vista, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williams" authorityYear="1973" box="[530,663,1905,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eriocerei">
<emphasis box="[530,663,1905,1928]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. eriocerei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
se asemeja a 
<taxonomicName authority="Willink &amp; González, 2018" authorityName="Willink &amp; González" authorityYear="2018" box="[835,984,1904,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dumetum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[835,984,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">P. dumetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[992,1058,1905,1928]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Se diferencian porque posee 1) antenas de 341–452 μm (499 μm en 
<taxonomicName authority="Willink &amp; González, 2018" authorityName="Willink &amp; González" authorityYear="2018" box="[632,781,217,241]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dumetum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[632,781,217,241]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. dumetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[787,853,218,242]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), fémur de 217–267 μm (285 μm en 
<taxonomicName authority="Willink &amp; González, 2018" authorityName="Willink &amp; González" authorityYear="2018" box="[1291,1440,217,241]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dumetum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1291,1440,217,241]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. dumetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[192,256,251,275]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) y tibia de 237–284 μm (359 μm en 
<taxonomicName authority="Willink &amp; González, 2018" authorityName="Willink &amp; González" authorityYear="2018" box="[690,839,251,275]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dumetum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[690,839,251,275]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. dumetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[845,911,251,275]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); 2) conductos con collar oral ausentes en el dorso (submarginales en dorso en 
<taxonomicName authority="Willink &amp; González, 2018" authorityName="Willink &amp; González" authorityYear="2018" box="[602,751,284,308]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dumetum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[602,751,284,308]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. dumetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[757,822,285,309]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); 3) conductos con collar oral en cefalotórax ventral muy escasos (numerosos en 
<taxonomicName authority="Willink &amp; González, 2018" authorityName="Willink &amp; González" authorityYear="2018" box="[535,684,317,341]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dumetum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[535,684,317,341]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. dumetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[691,758,318,342]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); y 4) poros multiloculares hasta segmento IV (hasta VI en 
<taxonomicName authority="Willink &amp; González, 2018" authorityName="Willink &amp; González" authorityYear="2018" box="[229,378,351,375]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Pseudococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dumetum" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[229,378,351,375]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">P. dumetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[385,452,351,375]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
